Abstract

Internationalisation which has been a loosely used term and has been used indifferently due to the increasing popularity of export mediations, which have been studied excessively over time. This paper focuses on a comparative analysis of the two methods of international expansion of Australian Business entities. Comparative methodology has been adopted that reviews time-consuming steps involved in the exporting process and expanding overseas through takeovers When it comes to universes, comparison always focuses on a definition of the “Variable” and an explanation of what factors will be compared. This Master thesis programme emphasizes the study of academic and theoretical approaches of minimum two previous studies. The international business related literature it is applied to an understanding of how these have come together to provide a macro framework that proves internationalisation of value chain in firms, which highlight the international strategy pursued and the ultimate expansion method utilised.

1 INTRODUCTIONResuscitating the rising popularity of international trade and its expansion is gaining as a firm business source and a prominent tool used as a means of sourcing raw materials. This business plan that benefits from free trade agreements, liberalization benefits and effective equilibrating strategies by adopting either of the two over-expanding methods open up avenues for several advantages, opportunities, growth and expansion.
